9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 738, L.D. 1868, “An Act to Advance a
10 Clean Energy Economy by Updating Renewable and Clean Resource Procurement Laws”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of sections 1, 2 and 3.
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 6 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 6. 35-A MRSA §3210, sub-§2, ¶A-4 is enacted to read:
14 A-4. "Class III resource" or "clean resource" means a source of generation that
15 generates power that can physically be delivered to the control region in which the New
16 England Power Pool, or its successor as approved by the Federal Energy Regulatory
17 Commission, has authority over transmission, or to the Maritimes Control Area and:
18 (1) Is a Class I resource or a Class IA resource;
19 (2) Relies on a nuclear power plant or hydroelectric generator that meets all state
20 and federal fish passage requirements applicable to the generator; or
21 (3) Generates electric energy in a manner that, as determined by the Department
22 of Environmental Protection, produces no more than a de minimis level of net
23 greenhouse gas emissions and co-pollutant emissions at the point of generation and
24 from the fuel supply chain of the facility and has been certified by the Governor's
25 Energy Office in accordance with rules adopted by the Department of
26 Environmental Protection in accordance with this subsection.'
27 Amend the bill in section 9 in the blocked paragraph in the 2nd line (page 3, line 27 in
28 L.D.) by striking out the following: "or order"
29 Amend the bill in section 10 in paragraph A in the blocked paragraph in the last line
30 (page 4, line 30 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "or" and inserting the following:
31 'or,'
32 Amend the bill in section 10 in paragraph A in the blocked paragraph in the last line
33 (page 4, line 30 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "3-A" the following: 'or 3-D'
